### SSE Streaming — commit b2fde5b
All 17 apps converted from /v1/generate (blocking JSON) to /v1/stream (SSE).
Users now see AI typing in real time instead of waiting for a response blob.

Shared streamSSE() helper injected into every app:
  - Opens fetch to /v1/stream
  - Reads response body as a ReadableStream
  - Parses SSE lines (`data: {...}`)
  - Extracts text chunks from Gemini candidate parts
  - Calls onChunk(chunk, fullSoFar) on every chunk

Behavior by app type:
  Text-output apps (mailKai, coverKai): text streams directly into output box
  JSON-output apps (all others): status shows "✦ N chars…" ticking up in
  real time; full JSON parsed + rendered when stream completes

Apps with 2 generate calls converted (mathKai): both fetchHint and
fetchFullSolution now stream independently.

Multimodal apps (recipeKai, diagramKai, readKai): contents[] format preserved
inside streamSSE body; streaming works with image+text payloads.

